  "notes": "Root element has classes 'logos logos-homehub full-width' — all three must be hardcoded. Each logo item renders as an <a> when href is provided, otherwise as a <span>. The .home-hub-logos element wraps a div.media--image--figure containing a figure.imgcapt with a picture element. Scroll arrows (when shown) are rendered as a div.scrollarrows with button.left (aria-label='Scroll left') and button.right (aria-label='Scroll right') containing Font Awesome icons. The logo-container content is often dynamically populated in production — the component renders whatever logos are passed as props. The 'full-width' class appears on all observed instances.",
  "htmlExamples": ["2554_4930", "2558_480", "2558_11322", "2558_19075"]
